item.description:
Javascript timer function can make some code be excueted repeatedly over time.
Syntax:
// open setInterval(function,interaval-time) // close let t = setInterval(function,interaval-time) clearInterval(t) t: variable
interaval-time unit: ms
Example:
&lt;body&gt; &lt;button class=&#34;btn&#34; disabled&gt;aggree(5)&lt;/button&gt; &lt;script&gt; const btn = document.querySelector(&#39;.btn&#39;) let i = 5 let timer = setInterval(function(){ i-- btn.innerHTML = `aggree(${i})` if (i === 0){ clearInterval(timer) btn.disabled = false btn.innerHTML = &#39;aggree&#39; } },1000) &lt;/script&gt; &lt;/body&gt;
